M|web-design-guidelines|name: web-design-guidelines
M|web-design-guidelines|description: >-
M|web-design-guidelines|rv UI code for Web Interface Guidelines compliance. Use when asked to "rv my UI", "check accessibility", "audit design", "rv UX", or "check my site against best practices".
M|web-design-guidelines|version: 1.0.0
M|web-design-guidelines|platforms: []
M|web-design-guidelines|metadata:
M|web-design-guidelines|hermes:
M|web-design-guidelines|tags: [frontend, react, tailwind, ui, component, design-system, ux, dev]
M|web-design-guidelines|author: vercel
M|web-design-guidelines|version: "1.0.0"
M|web-design-guidelines|argument-hint: <file-or-pattern>
M|web-design-guidelines|rv files for compliance with Web Interface Guidelines.
M|web-design-guidelines|1. Fetch the latest guidelines from the source URL below
M|web-design-guidelines|2. Read the specified files (or prompt user for files/pattern)
M|web-design-guidelines|3. Check against all rules in the fetched guidelines
M|web-design-guidelines|4. Output findings in the terse `file:line` format
M|web-design-guidelines|Fetch fresh guidelines before each rv:
M|web-design-guidelines|```
M|web-design-guidelines|https://raw.githubusercontent.com/vercel-labs/web-interface-guidelines/main/command.md
M|web-design-guidelines|```
M|web-design-guidelines|Use WebFetch to retrieve the latest rules. The fetched cnt contains all the rules and output format instructions.
M|web-design-guidelines|When a user provides a file or pattern argument:
M|web-design-guidelines|1. Fetch guidelines from the source URL above
M|web-design-guidelines|2. Read the specified files
M|web-design-guidelines|3. Apply all rules from the fetched guidelines
M|web-design-guidelines|4. Output findings using the format specified in the guidelines
M|web-design-guidelines|If no files specified, ask the user which files to rv.